<subSubSection id="209E1AAD0D6FB26DFF36FCBAFDC4140D" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF36FCBAFDC4140D" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36FCBAFEBF1469" bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for James (Jim) Cope (JSCC), who collected all three known specimens. The epithet is a noun in the genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
